humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that 3 out of 5 assessed lymph nodes are positive for metastasis (Axillary 3/5). Based on the new rules provided, N1 indicates metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes. Therefore, the N stage for this patient's cancer is N1.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The patient has 3/5 axillary lymph nodes positive for metastasis, which corresponds to a pathologic N1 stage. The report does not mention extracapsular invasion, so we cannot consider that in the staging. The exact number of positive lymph nodes may affect substaging, but for the main N stage, N1 is appropriate.
